02446nam a22003493i 20180904112500.0m     o  d        cr unu||||||||180308s2018    miu     ob    001 0 eng    a9780472124015q(electronic book)  a0472124013q(electronic book)  z9780472130894q(hardcover)7 a10.3998/mpub.99097832doi  aMiUbengepnerdacMiU14aHQ1073b.D87 20181 aDurnová, Anna,eauthor.14aThe politics of intimacy :brethinking the end-of-life controversy /cAnna Durnová. 1aAnn Arbor, Michigan :bUniversity of Michigan Press,c[2018]  a1 online resource (xv, 285 pages).  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier1 aConfigurations : critical studies of world politics  aIncludes bibliographical references and index.  aDebates on the end-of-life controversy are complex because they seem to highjack national and cultural traditions. Where previous books have focused on ideological grounds, The Politics of Intimacy explores dying as the site where policies are negotiated and implemented. Intimacy comprises the emotional experience of the end of life and how we acknowledge it-or not-through institutions. This process shows that end-of-life controversy relies on the conflict between the individual and these institutions, a relationship that is the cornerstone of Western liberal democracies. Through interviews with mourners, stakeholders, and medical professionals, examination of media debates in France and the Czech Republic, Durnová shows that liberal institutions, in their attempts to accommodate the emotional experience at the end of life, ultimately fail. She describes this deadlock as the "politics of intimacy," revealing that political institutions deploy power through collective acknowledgment of individual emotions but fail to maintain this recognition because of this same experience.  aDescription based on information from the publisher. 0aDeath. 0aIntimacy (Psychology) 4aElectronic books.2 aMichigan Publishing (University of Michigan)epublisher. 0aConfigurations (Ann Arbor, Mich.)40zAccess to the Michigan Publishing online version:uhttps://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.9909783